This page documents the Japanese text table used in Final Fantasy USA: Mystic Quest (Japanese version).

==Overview==

The Japanese version uses a text table loaded into VRAM at '''$6200-$6fff'''. Unlike the Western versions which use DTE compression, the Japanese version uses direct kana character mappings:
* '''Hiragana''' ($4b-$5e, $80-$b1): Basic hiragana characters with dakuten/handakuten variants
* '''Katakana''' ($60-$7d, $b8-$ef): Basic katakana characters with dakuten/handakuten variants
* '''Numbers and punctuation''' ($f0-$fc): 0-9, !, ?, …
* '''Space character''': $ff

